A_458 - People of foreign nationality, when they settle in a country, sometimes have difficulty reasoning correctly, feeling at ease and making decisions that may also prove correct from a work and entrepreneurial point of view. If on the one hand it is true that they improve the biodiversity of an area, on the other it is equally true that their working or personal life, in the absence of sufficient supports, could prove difficult or not very fruitful. However, if you decide to host some of them or try to live together, know that additional caution and patience may be necessary precisely because of their disorientation. For these people, the use of excessively virtual experiences in solitude could also be dangerous: it is better to practice sports in company than to play video games alone.